File: Authorities say the fire was caused by overloading due to illegal connections. JOHANNESBURG - A mini-substation in Alexandra has caught fire. Authorities say the fire was caused by overloading due to illegal connections. The incident took place on the corner of 16th Avenue and Joe Nhlanhla Street. READ: Power system under severe pressure - Eskom More residents will have to spend the cold front in the dark, as City Power tries to fix the situation. This is the fourth mini-substation damaged since the start of June.